                     <namePart>Hormann, Irmgard.</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/cre">Creator</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>Hörmann, Helmuth Winfrid, 1908-</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/cre">Creator</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>Cartwright, James F.</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/cre">Creator</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>Irmgard and Helmuth Hormann memorabilia of student years, 1927-1944 1927-1937.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>The Memorabilia Collection contains two scrapbooks. One documents Helmuth's drama roles at the University of Hawaii and community theater in Honolulu. The other documents Irmgard's experiences at UH. A separate box of photographs cover various activities Irmgard participated in, including the Asilomar Conference, Institute of Pacific Relations Youth Conference, a trip to Maui with a group of student friends, and graduation. Several copies of Hawaii Quill, which Irmgard edited for a year (two issues) also are in the collection. Finally the collection contains a photograph of the wedding party of Katsuso Miho (one of the group of student friends who traveled to Maui) and Alice Dame at Church of the Crossroads in Honolulu in 1944 and a photocopy of an article about the wedding from The Friend. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>University of Hawaii at Manoa</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>

resource.abstract: The Memorabilia Collection contains two scrapbooks. One documents Helmuth's drama roles at the University of Hawaii and community theater in Honolulu. The other documents Irmgard's experiences at UH. A separate box of photographs cover various activities Irmgard participated in, including the Asilomar Conference, Institute of Pacific Relations Youth Conference, a trip to Maui with a group of student friends, and graduation. Several copies of Hawaii Quill, which Irmgard edited for a year (two issues) also are in the collection. Finally the collection contains a photograph of the wedding party of Katsuso Miho (one of the group of student friends who traveled to Maui) and Alice Dame at Church of the Crossroads in Honolulu in 1944 and a photocopy of an article about the wedding from The Friend.

                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>John Mason Young architectural drawings, 1889-1949 1909-1939. 1889-1939.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>Consists of blueprints and blueline prints for building projects which Pacific Engineering Company, a company organized and directed by John Mason Young, beginning in 1908, over the approximately forty-one years of the company's existence. In addition the papers include drawings of College of Hawaii and University of Hawaii buildings and plans for development for which Young was responsible as college engineer. Buildings for which there are drawings in the papers include Hawaii Hall, then known as Main Building; Library, for which only one drawing seems to exist; Biological Sciences Building, now named Dean Hall; Social Sciences Building, now named Crawford Hall; Dramatics Laboratory, an addition to Farrington Hall, now demolished; Home Economics Laboratory, now named Miller Hall; and an undated but early grain drying facility. Drawings for other buildings in Honolulu built by Pacific Engineering include: Castle Hall, Punahou School; Blaisdell Hotel; Theo H. Davies block; Empire Theatre; Church of Christ, Scientist, Punahou Street; and the S.M. Damon Building (also known as Bishop Bank, Bishop Trust, and First Hawaiian Bank). </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>University of Hawaii at Manoa</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>
